The paper discusses adversarial machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on generative adversarial networks (GANs) and deep learning suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses attacks on machine learning systems, which falls under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of APIs and the focus on text classification suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories. Finally, the use of GANs for generating synthetic training data suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
